  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Operations & Recruitment Support Executive",
  "description": "<p>The attachment aims to equip the participant with practical administrative and recruitment support skills through structured on-the-job training.</p><p>The participant will be trained to support daily operations, documentation, coordination and compliance-related tasks within a manpower agency environment.</p><p>This attachment supports the participant’s mid-career transition by building transferable skills that enhance employability in administrative and operations support roles<br /></p><p>• Support screening and shortlisting of domestic worker candidates</p><p>• Assist in interview coordination and basic training support</p><p>• Prepare candidate profiles, resumes and related documentation</p><p>• Support matching and placement coordination between candidates and employers</p><p>• Assist with MOM documentation and compliance requirements</p><p>• Support onboarding and entry processes for domestic workers</p><p>• Follow up on employer requests and service coordination</p><p>• Maintain records and update internal tracking systems<br /></p><p><br />• Administrative and office operations skills</p><p>• Documentation and record management</p><p>• Basic recruitment coordination and candidate profiling</p><p>• Use of internal systems and digital tools</p><p>• Understanding of compliance and regulatory documentation</p><p>• Client communication and coordination skills</p><p>• Time management and workplace communication<br /></p><p><br />Duration of Attachment:  6 months</p>",
